					<head>Compendium</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842" rend="visible">
						<summary>The main principles contained in Isaac Alfasi's compendium on the treatises Ta'anit and Shabat, compiled by Aaron Berechiah of Modena.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842">
							<locus from="1r" to="126v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Kelale hilkhot ha-Ri"f </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">כללי הלכות הרי"ף</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90404354">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90404354" xml:lang="en">Aaron Berechiah ben Moses, of Modena, 1549-1639</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90404354" xml:lang="he">מודנה, אהרן ברכיה בן משה </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>There is an autograph description of the work on the vellum flyleaf at the beginning of the manuscript, folio 1v.</p>
								<p>The editions of Alfasi used by Aron Berechiah were those of Riva di Trento and Sabionetta, see e.g. folio 3r (margin), 1r, 52r. </p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="table">Tables of avot.<locus from="123r" to="126v"/>
							</decoNote>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>126 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>202</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>160</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>126 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 modern paper and 1 older vellum flyleaves at the end). Folio 1 is vellum.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Hard-point ruling visible.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. Running titles.</p>
									<p>Marginal notes.</p>
									<p>Folio 2 has been slightly folded.</p>
									<p>Folios 93r-121v are blank.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian cursive script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 2r contains some doodles.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Ish ger</name>, i.e. <name type="person" role="owner">Abraham Joseph S. Grazziano</name>: inscribed  (at the top of folio 3r).</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Camillo Jaghel</name>: inscribed with his name, 1613 (folio 92v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">50-56</ref>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Renato da Modena</name>: inscribed with his name, 1626 (folio 126v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">132-133</ref>.</p>
						</additions>
